					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Does your microcontroller have an SPI slave port? The NES controller protocol is really just a variant of SPI. The console can send bits by putting a voltage on the strobe wire (STA $4016) and sending clock pulses to one of the devices (LDA $4017). The Super NES Mouse, for example, uses this to send commands to change the sensitivity.<br /><br />What tool are you using to convert graphics to NES format?</div>

