				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The darlington transistors are not really necessary. It is easier to just set the pin to output a logic 0 and then change its mode to OUTPUT to pull the line low, and change it to INPUT to put it in a high-z state (no button pressed). However, the transistors make the design a little easier to adapt.</div>

